CPIP — Coffee Pot Internet Protocol
RFC 2324 (HTCPCP) + RFC 7168 + Mesh Extension

Next-gen IoT coffee control for Raspberry Pi with mesh networking. Controls real coffee makers via GPIO, discovers peers via mDNS/UDP, routes messages through Pi Zero mesh networks without internet. Includes web dashboard, SSE events, Prometheus metrics, brew scheduling, and a covert channel hidden in HTCPCP brew requests using a non-FIPS custom cipher.

Pots discover each other automatically. Messages store-and-forward through the mesh. Zero external Python dependencies. Runs on Pi Zero 2 WH.